Third-party components
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Sparkle (https://sparkle-project.org)
  Auto-update framework. MIT License. Fetched as a Swift Package dependency at
  build time; not vendored in this repository.

Wine (https://www.winehq.org)
  GameMaster downloads pre-built Wine runtimes at first run and when an app
  needs a different one. Wine is licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public
  License (LGPL) v2.1 or later. GameMaster does not modify Wine; every runtime
  download is pinned to an exact URL and SHA-256 digest.

Default runtime: "Game Porting Toolkit" community build by Gcenx
  (https://github.com/Gcenx/game-porting-toolkit)
  Downloaded directly from that project's GitHub releases. NOTE: this build
  ships with Apple's proprietary D3DMetal evaluation libraries included, as
  packaged and distributed by that project — see the Apple section below.
  GameMaster does not re-host this archive.

Steam run runtime: GameMaster runtime asset
  (gamemaster-runtime-sikarugir-*.tar.xz on this project's GitHub releases)
  An aggregate assembled by scripts/assemble-steam-runtime.sh from three
  unmodified, SHA-256-pinned upstream archives:
  - Sikarugir Wine engine (https://github.com/Sikarugir-App/Engines) — a
    CrossOver-derived Wine build, LGPL v2.1 or later. Sources available from
    the Sikarugir project and https://www.codeweavers.com/crossover/source.
  - Sikarugir Wrapper Template support dylibs
    (https://github.com/Sikarugir-App/Wrapper) — runtime libraries the engine
    links against (e.g. libinotify); licenses of the respective upstreams.
  - DXMT (https://github.com/3Shain/dxmt) — Metal-based implementation of
    Direct3D 10/11 for macOS/Wine. Copyright Feifan He for CodeWeavers,
    LGPL v2.1 or later.
  The assembly script documents the exact byte-for-byte inputs; no binary is
  modified during assembly. The archive carries the applicable license texts
  (wswine.bundle/licenses/) and a per-component THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.txt with
  source-code pointers, vendored from scripts/licenses/ in this repository.

steamwebhelper wrapper (Tools/SteamWebHelperWrapper)
  The approach of wrapping steamwebhelper.exe to inject CEF compatibility
  flags is adapted from the open-source Vineport project (MIT License);
  the wrapper here is an independent reimplementation.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Apple Game Porting Toolkit / D3DMetal
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Apple's D3DMetal libraries and the Game Porting Toolkit "Evaluation
environment for Windows games" are proprietary to Apple Inc. and subject to
Apple's own license terms.

GameMaster does NOT re-host, mirror, or bundle these libraries in this
repository or in its own release assets. Two paths can place them on a user's
machine:

1. The default runtime above is a community build that includes them as
   distributed by the Gcenx project; GameMaster downloads that archive from
   the project's own releases.
2. The user may optionally import a newer version from the "Evaluation
   environment for Windows games" disk image they download from
   developer.apple.com themselves. GameMaster verifies the payload is signed
   by Apple before importing; the libraries remain solely on the user's
   machine.

